HB 584 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Boyd
Abstract: Provides for the privileges of foster children to have proper luggage to move
between foster homes instead of garbage bags, the responsibilities of local social
services districts to provide proper luggage, the responsibilities of host families to
ensure that the luggage remains with the children, and provides for expanding the
age range of foster children covered under these provisions.
Proposed law changes all mention of the words "right" and "rights" to "privilege" and
"privileges" in the applicable statute.
Proposed law expands the age range of fourteen through eighteen to zero through eighteen.
Proposed law provides foster children the privilege to proper luggage when moving between
foster homes to ensure their dignity and safety.
Proposed law defines luggage and specifies the condition the luggage must be in.
Proposed law strictly prohibits the use of garbage bags as luggage for foster children.
Proposed law provides for the responsibilities of local social services districts to provide
foster children with proper luggage.
Proposed law provides for the responsibilities of host families to ensure that luggage remains
with the children.
Proposed law provides for local social service districts and DCFS to host biennial luggage
donation drives for luggage to be distributed to foster children.
(Amends R.S. 46:286.16)
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
